title: 'Good transfer speeds
body: '4.0 out of 5 stars'Sequential read speeds are as advertised, write speeds are also decent. The price is a bit on the higher side (got it for Rs. 629), but the main downside is that the aluminium body gets really hot really quickly, to the point where you can't hold it for more than 3-4 seconds. Apparently the drive itself doesn't get damaged according to other forums, but I'm more worried about the USB port on my PC.
